<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2684] TestMasterWrongRS flaky in trunk</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2684</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I think this is just a flaky test. I saw:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.lang.AssertionError: expected:&amp;lt;2&amp;gt; but was:&amp;lt;3&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
on the first:&lt;br/&gt;
    assertEquals(2, cluster.getLiveRegionServerThreads().size());&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My guess is that the 2 second sleep is not good enough. We should probably either force a heartbeat somehow, or hook in so we can wait until there&apos;s been a heartbeat, rather than sleeping a hardcoded amount of time.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
